# HTML standards

Full checklist: `docs/static-site-standards.md` (HTML5, SEO meta, link safety).

## Document shell

- `<!DOCTYPE html>`, `<html lang="en">` (adjust locale if needed)
- `<meta charset="utf-8">`, viewport meta, UTF-8 throughout
- One logical `<h1>` per page; heading levels never skip (h1→h2→h3…)

## Semantics & landmarks

- Use `<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<article>`, `<section>`, `<aside>`, `<footer>`
- Prefer `<dialog>`, `<details>`/`<summary>`, `<figure>`/`<figcaption>`, `<time>`, `<mark>`, `<abbr>` where appropriate
- `<picture>` + `<source>` for WebP/AVIF; `width`/`height` on images (CLS)
- `<template>` / `<slot>` for Web Components; microdata/`itemprop` when useful

## Head (every page)

- Unique `<title>` and `<meta name="description">`
- `<link rel="canonical" href="…">`
- Open Graph + Twitter Cards (valid `property`/`name`; OG image 1200×630)
- JSON-LD (`WebSite`, `Organization`, `BreadcrumbList`, `Article`, `Person` as relevant)

## UX / a11y hooks

- Skip link as first focusable element in `<body>`
- External `target="_blank"`: `rel="noopener noreferrer"`; `nofollow`/`rel="me"` when appropriate

## Scripts

- New scripts: `<script type="module" defer src="…">` — not inline polyfills unless critical
